<div class="post">
	<div class="titolo">
		<h2><a href="http://www.softwareishard.com/blog/planet-mozilla/firebug-tip-using-command-line-within-an-iframe/">Firebug Tip: using command line within an iframe</a></h2>
  		<small>by Honza</small>
	</div>
  	<span class="edit"></span>

  	<div class="corpo">
  	  	<ul class="more_info">
  	  		<li class="first"><strong>Published</strong>:<span>February 17th, 2011</span></li>
  	  		<li><strong>Comments</strong>:<span><a href="http://www.softwareishard.com/blog/planet-mozilla/firebug-tip-using-command-line-within-an-iframe/#comments ">10 Comments</a></span></li>
  	 		<li><strong>Category</strong>:<span><a href="http://www.softwareishard.com/blog/category/firebug-tip/" title="View all posts in Firebug Tip" rel="category tag">Firebug Tip</a>, <a href="http://www.softwareishard.com/blog/category/planet-mozilla/" title="View all posts in Planet Mozilla" rel="category tag">Planet Mozilla</a></span></li>
  	  	</ul>
		<p>Firebug <strong>command line</strong> allows executing JavaScript expressions within context of the current page. Firebug also provides a set of built in <a href="http://getfirebug.com/wiki/index.php/Command_Line_API">APIs</a> and one of them is <code>cd()</code>.</p>
<p><code>cd(window)</code> <em>By default, command line expressions are relative to the top-level window of the page, cd() allows you to use the window of a frame in the page instead.</em></p>
<p>There is several ways how to use this method. First, let's imagine following page:</p>
<div class="dean_ch" style="white-space: wrap;">
<span class="sc3"><span class="re1">&lt;html</span> <span class="re0">xmlns</span>=<span class="st0">&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml&quot;</span><span class="re2">&gt;</span></span><br />
<span class="sc3"><span class="re1">&lt;head<span class="re2">&gt;</span></span></span><br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; <span class="sc3"><span class="re1">&lt;title<span class="re2">&gt;</span></span></span>Console Test Page<span class="sc3"><span class="re1">&lt;/title<span class="re2">&gt;</span></span></span><br />
<span class="sc3"><span class="re1">&lt;/head<span class="re2">&gt;</span></span></span><br />
<span class="sc3"><span class="re1">&lt;body<span class="re2">&gt;</span></span></span><br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; <span class="sc3"><span class="re1">&lt;iframe</span> <span class="re0">id</span>=<span class="st0">&quot;frameID&quot;</span> <span class="re0">name</span>=<span class="st0">&quot;frameName&quot;</span> <span class="re0">src</span>=<span class="st0">&quot;iframe.html&quot;</span> <span class="re2">/&gt;</span></span><br />
<span class="sc3"><span class="re1">&lt;/body<span class="re2">&gt;</span></span></span><br />
<span class="sc3"><span class="re1">&lt;/html<span class="re2">&gt;</span></span></span></div>
<ul>
<li><code>cd(document.getElementById("frameID").contentWindow);</code> switch to a frame by ID</li>
<li><code>cd(window.frames[0]);</code> switch to the first frame in the list of frames</li>
<li><code>cd(window.frames["frameName"]);</code> switch to a frame using by name</li>
<li><code>cd(window.top);</code> switching back to the top level window</li>
</ul>
<p><img src="http://softwareishard.com/firebug/tips/iframe-command-line/command-line.png" /></p>
<p>Check the example page <a href="http://softwareishard.com/firebug/tips/iframe-command-line/consoletest.html">online</a>.</p>
<p class="firebugTipsLink">See all <a href="http://www.softwareishard.com/blog/firebug-tips/">Firebug tips</a><br />
		<div class="clear"></div>
  	</div> 
</div>


